Reference information:
The following dependencies, setup and configuration instructions are to 
be considered suggestions, not rules.  It is quite possible to use for example
SQLite as database engine instead of MySQL, &c.

Dependencies:
* Django-1.3.1
   < http://www.djangoproject.com/download/ >
* mysql and mysql-server
   < http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/ >
* MySQL-python
   < http://sourceforge.net/projects/mysql-python/ >
* Tastypie
   < https://github.com/toastdriven/django-tastypie >
   < http://django-tastypie.readthedocs.org/en/latest/tutorial.html#installation >

Setup:
Create a project:
$ django-admin.py startproject mysite
$ cd mysite/
$ git clone https://github.com/reggna/Curo.git

Create a database and a user with access to it
$ mysql -u root -p
Enter password:
mysql> create database curo;
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> create user 'curo'@'localhost' identified by 'curo';
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
mysql> grant alter, create, delete, drop, index, insert, select on curo.* to 'curo'@'localhost';
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)

Replace the database settings in mysite/settings.py with the following lines:
DATABASES = {
    'default': {
        'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
        'NAME': 'curo',
        'USER': 'curo',
        'PASSWORD': 'curo',
        'HOST': '',
        'PORT': '',
    }
}

Add "'Curo'" to the list of INSTALLED_APPS and replace the ROOT_URLCONF
to search in Curo instead of mysite.

Sync the models to the database:
$ python manage.py syncdb

Start the server:
$ python manage.py runserver

